<subSubSection id="02C66578FFFDFFBCFF3D9FB16804798E" pageId="16" pageNumber="30" type="discussion">
<paragraph id="4A6336F3FFFDFFBCFF3D9FB16B5E794C" blockId="16.[151,756,1013,1263]" pageId="16" pageNumber="30">
<emphasis id="78A8EAE1FFFDFFBCFF3D9FB16805796C" bold="true" box="[151,264,1013,1037]" pageId="16" pageNumber="30">Remarks:</emphasis>
It resembles the specimens recorded by LE ROY (1953) and SAID &amp; KENAWY (1956).
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="4A6336F3FFFDFFBCFF3D98716804798E" blockId="16.[151,756,1013,1263]" pageId="16" pageNumber="30">
<emphasis id="78A8EAE1FFFDFFBCFF3D987168C4792C" bold="true" box="[151,457,1077,1101]" pageId="16" pageNumber="30">Stratigraphic distribution:</emphasis>
It was originally described from the basal Eocene of the Maqfi Section by LE ROY (1953), but it may be extended from the Maastrichtian to the Paleocene (SAID &amp; KENAWY, 1956). In the study area, it is recorded in the Maastrichtian and Paleocene sediments.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
